The diagonal, d, of a square with sides of length s is
 $$d=s \sqrt{2}$$
. If the diagonal is $$10 \sqrt{2}$$
, then
 \begin{align}
   10 \sqrt{2}
    &=s \sqrt{2} \\
     \frac{10 \sqrt{2}}{\sqrt{2}}
       &=\frac{s \sqrt{2}}{\sqrt{2}} \\
       \\ \therefore \quad s
& =10 \text{ cm}
 \end{align}
